                    <strong>ℹ️ Good to Know:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 10px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li><strong>Duration:</strong> 2 hours total hammam ritual + massage</li>
                        <li><strong>Separate sessions:</strong> Men and women have completely separate areas and attendants</li>
                        <li><strong>Privacy:</strong> You wear disposable undergarments (or swimsuit) throughout - not fully naked</li>
                        <li><strong>Intensity:</strong> Exfoliation can be vigorous - communicate your comfort level!</li>
                        <li><strong>Skin results:</strong> Expect incredibly soft, glowing skin that lasts days</li>
                        <li><strong>Not suitable for:</strong> Pregnant women, severe skin conditions, recent sunburn</li>
                        <li><strong>Best timing:</strong> Book for afternoon/evening after beach activities</li>
                        <li><strong>Free cancellation:</strong> Cancel up to 24 hours before for full refund</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div style="background: #e8f5e9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #8B5CF6;">
                    <strong>💡 Local Insider Tips:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 10px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li>Don't shave 24 hours before - the exfoliation can irritate freshly shaved skin</li>
                        <li>Hydrate well before and after - you'll sweat a lot in the steam!</li>
                        <li>Embrace the tradition - let attendant do their work, it's supposed to be vigorous!</li>
                        <li>Book private session for first-timers if feeling shy about shared hammam</li>
                        <li>Your skin will be sensitive after - avoid sun exposure for 24 hours</li>
                        <li>The hammam is best AFTER beach days, not before (you'll get dirty/sandy)</li>
                        <li>Tip your attendant 20-50 MAD if you enjoyed the service</li>
                        <li>Buy argan oil products at the hammam - usually authentic and good prices</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
